      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 12: The script writes the partial plist to a fixed path in /tmp. This can clobber another user\u0027s file or fail unpredictably on shared build machines. Use mktemp and clean it up with a trap, for example:\n```suggestion\nPARTIAL_PLIST\u003d\"$(mktemp \"${TMPDIR:-/tmp}/jami-partial.XXXXXX.plist\")\"\ntrap \u0027rm -f \"${PARTIAL_PLIST}\"\u0027 EXIT\nxcrun actool AppIcon.icon --compile . --app-icon AppIcon \\\n  --include-all-app-icons --enable-on-demand-resources NO \\\n  --target-device mac --platform macosx \\\n  --minimum-deployment-target 13.0 \\\n  --output-partial-info-plist \"${PARTIAL_PLIST}\"\n```",
      "revId": "ae924af915c1161239097cb86ab6567d43b3cb2b",
